<!DOCTYPE book PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DocBook XML V4.5//EN" "http://www.oasis-open.org/docbook/xml/4.5/docbookx.dtd">
<section>
	<title>Platform specific generators</title>
	<para>
		These are pre-configured generators for special platforms or
		languages. Use
		these if the default values are ok for you and/or you
		don't
		want to configure
		everything all by yourself. These generators
		should
		satisfy most
		needs. But of course you can also change the
		configuration
		of these
		generators if you want to. They are all
		subclasses from the
		<link
			linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.DefaultGenerator">
			<literal>DefaultGenerator</literal>
		</link>
		and therefore inherit also all of its parameters and setting most of
		them by default.
		Especially
		<link
			linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.template">
			<literal>template</literal>
		</link>
		,
		<link
			linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.typeMappingFile">
			<literal>typeMappingFile</literal>
		</link>
		,
		<link linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.generator.importRegex">
			<literal>importRegex</literal>
		</link>
		and
		<link linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.generator.fileExtensions">
			<literal>fileExtensions</literal>
		</link>
		are set by default.
		In fact to run these generators you only need to
		set the
		<link
			linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.outputDir">
			<literal>outputDir</literal>
		</link>
		.
	</para>
	<section id="en.genesez.core.configuration.platforms.JavaGenerator">
		<title>JavaGenerator</title>
		<para>
			The JavaGenerator generates Java 5 source code from a GeneSEZ
			model by default. It can be added to the workflow with
			<programlisting><![CDATA[<component id="model2java" class="org.genesez.platforms.java.workflow.JavaGenerator">]]></programlisting>
		</para>
		<variablelist>
			<varlistentry>
				<term>
					<link
						linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.template">template</link>
				</term>
				<term>
					<emphasis>single-value</emphasis>
				</term>
				<term>
					default:
					<literal>
						de::genesez::platforms::java::java5::templates::Root::Root
					</literal>
				</term>
				<listitem>
					<para>XPand-Template for model-to-java
						transformation.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
				<term>
					<link
						linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.typeMappingFile">typeMappingFile</link>
				</term>
				<term>
					<emphasis>multi-value</emphasis>
				</term>
				<term>
					default:
					<literal>
						de/genesez/platforms/java/typemapping/typemapping.xml
					</literal>
				</term>
				<listitem>
					<para>Default java type-mapping file.</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
				<term>formatterConfig</term>
				<term>
					<emphasis>single-value</emphasis>
				</term>
				<term>
					default:
					<literal>
						de/genesez/platforms/java/workflow/eclipse.java.formatter.settings.xml
					</literal>
				</term>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						specification file for configuration of the JavaBeautifier.
						Currently the
						integrated formatter from eclipse is used.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
				<term>newAssociationHandling</term>
				<term>
					<emphasis>single-value</emphasis>
				</term>
				<term>
					default:
					<literal>true</literal>
				</term>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						If true the GeneSEZ specific association handling will be used,
						else the one from the JavaBean pattern.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
				<term>fieldAccess</term>
				<term>
					<emphasis>single-value</emphasis>
				</term>
				<term>
					default:
					<literal>true</literal>
				</term>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						If true annotations will be placed onto the attributes, else
						onto the methods.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
		</variablelist>
	</section>
</section>